%dl.dl-horizontal
  %dt Audio and Timing
  %dd
    %p Greatly improved downmixing for audio with more than 2 channels
    %p Also move karaoke markers after the dragged marker if Ctrl is held down (#{ticket 1557})
    %p Improve Unicode support in the karaoke split/join bar
    %p Report a more useful line number for bad lines in the Timing Post Processor (#{ticket 1596})
    %p Default to only showing the maximum in the waveform view
    %p When zooming the audio display with the scroll wheel, zoom into the mouse's position rather than the center of the display
    %p Significantly improve the automatic matching in the kanji timer
    %p Skip empty lines when copying karaoke timing

  %dt Automation
  %dd
    %p Fix crash when something other than a string is passed to error()
    %p Match HTML colors in a way that actually works in extract_color (#{ticket 1575})
    %p Implement the "coloralpha" automation control type
    %p Switch the re module from wxRegex to boost.regex and fix a bunch of bugs
    %p Drop support for non-UTF-8 scripts
    %p The subtitles object can now be iterated over with ipairs as if it were a normal table
    %p Add native support for MoonScript
    %p Add support for using standard button ID in dialogs (#{ticket 1609})
    %p Load autoloaded automation scripts in parallel for slightly faster startup
    %p Improve error reporting and actually include a stack trace
    %p Double the size of the log window
    %p Make it harder to break the included modules by defining a global function with the same name as a lua built-in
    %p Trying to log a string which could be converted to a number now works correctly
    %p Return full paths from aegisub.dialog.open and aegisub.dialog.save rather than just the filename

  %dt Autosave
  %dd
    %p Create new files each time when autosaving so that opening an old version of a file after a crash doesn't overwrite the newer autosaved version (#{ticket 1155})
    %p Add a dialog for opening autosave and crash recovery files rather than having to dig around in %APPDATA%\Aegisub (#{ticket 781})

  %dt Find/Replace
  %dd
    %p Case insensitive find now works for all languages rather than just things sufficiently English-like (#{ticket 1342})
    %p Add an option to skip override tags (##{ticket 104})
    %p Add an option to skip comments (##{ticket 683})
    %p Actually obey the "In Selection" option for things other than Replace All if multiple lines are selected
    %p Search from the position of the character rather than the position of the last thing found
    %p Remove the "update video" option since it didn't actually do anything

  %dt Fonts Collector
  %dd
    %p Improve reporting when a font is missing a whitespace character used in the script (#{ticket 1553})
    %p Fix some cases where the wrong font was being selected
    %p Show a more useful error message when the style used by a subtitle doesn't exist

  %dt Performance
  %dd
    %p Significantly reduce the performance penalty of ASS Attachments
    %p Vastly cut down on memory usage with large subtitle files
    %p Speed up committing changes a bit
    %p More work is done on background threads to avoid blocking the UI
    %p Improve indexing performance
    %p Prefetch the font list for the style editor to make it open much faster on systems with large numbers of fonts installed

  %dt OS X
  %dd
    %p Add partial HiDPI support
    %p Use the native placeholder text functionality rather than the custom logic which worked slightly differently
    %p Make it sort of possible but awkward to set hotkeys (#{ticket 1589})
    %p Properly handle dead keys in the edit box (but still not IMEs)
    %p Fix a bunch of CoreText warnings on 10.9
    %p Sign the binary to avoid Gatekeeper warnings on 10.8+

  %dt Spellchecking
  %dd
    %p Updated from hunspell 1.2.1 to 1.3.2 on Windows
    %p Improve spellchecker word splitting (#{ticket 1206})
    %p Allow removing added words from the dictionary (#{ticket 1184})
    %p Add an option to ignore uppercase words (#{ticket 1460})

  %dt Stuff
  %dd
    %p Fix changing the MRU limit for subtitle files (#{ticket 1592})
    %p Actually select the correct lines in the select overlaps macro (#{ticket 1594})
    %p Fix loading keyframe files with Windows newlines on non-Windows platforms
    %p Add support for ffmpeg/avconv's keyframe format
    %p Add support for the scroll wheel to the video slider
    %p Eliminate a bogus limit of 100 for a bunch of rarely-used options
    %p Add Backspace to the keys that commands can be bound to (#{ticket 1631})
    %p Add support for the Windows 7 taskbar progress bar
    %p Make saving transient UI state in the file optional (#{ticket 1535})
    %p Improve support for locales which use a comma as the decimal separator

  %dt Subs Edit Box
  %dd
    %p The buttons in the main edit box can be hotkeyed
    %p By default, Alt+1-4 activate the appropriate color buttons
    %p Add alpha to the color picker dialog
    %p Add a character counter which shows the number of characters in the longest line of the currently selected subtitle
    %p Add an option to show the contents of the current line when it was first selected
    %p Make syntax highlighting better match VSFilter's parsing
    %p Always add the spellchecker language list to the context menu
    %p "Split line at cursor" can be hotkeyed
    %p Change the Effect box to a combobox like the Actor box (#{ticket 1461})
    %p Be less dumb when subtitles lines are pasted into the edit box

  %dt Subtitles Grid
  %dd
    %p Insert new lines before/after the active line rather than the first selected line
    %p The grid can be scrolled past the end of the file
    %p Paste over now replaces the selection if multiple lines are selected, since that's what most people seem to expect it to do
    %p Do a better job of picking a new active line after deleting lines (#{ticket 1595})
    %p Only paint the margin values in the grid if they're non-zero
    %p Replace "Duplicate and Shift by 1 Frame" with "Split lines at video position"

  %dt Subtitle Formats
  %dd
    %p Drop support for ASS2 since it didn't really work and no one used it
    %p Drop support for the "Collisions" property in ASS file since VSFilter doesn't support it
    %p Fix loading subtitles from Matroska files without track names
    %p Improve behavior when character set detection fails
    %p Add an option to not skip blank lines when importing plain text files
    %p Fix double-prompting to pick a character set in some cases (#{ticket 1512})
    %p Make the SRT parser more forgiving of malformed files (#{ticket 1614})
    %p Support loading subtitles from improperly concatenated matroska files
    %p Fix some issues with writing EBU STL files

  %dt Translations
  %dd
    %p Add Galician translation by Nuria Andi√≥n
    %p Actually add the translations to the desktop file on linux

  %dt Video
  %dd
    %p Drop MPC-HC VSFitler and default to xy-VSFilter now that CCCP has switched
    %p Honor the color matrix tag from the subtitles file when appropriate (#{ticket 1649})
    %p Update the title of the detached video dialog when videos are opened (#{ticket 1607})
    %p Add the command video/subtitles_provider/cycle, which can be hotkeyed to quickly switch between VSFilter and libass on Windows

  %dt Visual Typesetting Tools
  %dd
    %p Fix some cases where tags other than the one(s) being actively manipulated were being modified (#{ticket 1513})
    %p Update all selected rows in the clip tools rather than just the active line
    %p Lock aspect ratio in the scale tool when alt is held down
    %p Add box selection to the move mode of the vector clip tool (#{ticket 1404})
    %p Significantly speed up dragging lots of vector clip control points
    %p Make the X/Y rotation grid much bigger
    %p Apply the line's shear to the x/y rotation grid

